245
00:14:44,040 --> 00:14:45,980
You look beautiful in it.

246
00:14:48,220 --> 00:14:49,490
Your lips are chapped.

247
00:15:05,160 --> 00:15:09,420
I heard he's only doing one quad at 
the beginning this time, but...

248
00:15:09,420 --> 00:15:11,840
He hates making compromises, yeah.

249
00:15:12,140 --> 00:15:14,600
Good luck, Yuri-kun!

250
00:15:12,910 --> 00:15:17,330
Representing Ice Castle Hasetsu, 
please welcome Katsuki Yuri-san.

251
00:15:14,600 --> 00:15:17,330
For this first public performance 
of his free program,

252
00:15:17,330 --> 00:15:21,530
the music is an original composition 
expressing Katsuki's skating career,

253
00:15:21,530 --> 00:15:23,460
titled "Yuri on Ice."

254
00:15:23,460 --> 00:15:25,720
The program was choreographed 
by Victor Nikiforov.

255
00:15:37,330 --> 00:15:42,830
<i>This program starts off with the Yuri from 
back when he felt he was fighting alone.</i>

256
00:15:44,680 --> 00:15:47,080
<i>The first jump is a quad-triple combination.</i>

257
00:15:47,580 --> 00:15:50,760
<i>He's been landing it just fine during practice.</i>

258
00:15:54,930 --> 00:15:56,190
A quad-double!

259
00:15:56,190 --> 00:15:57,530
He nailed it!

260
00:15:59,080 --> 00:16:01,300
<i>He changed the triple to a double?</i>

261
00:16:01,300 --> 00:16:03,560
<i>He's changing the jump elements?</i>

262
00:16:04,780 --> 00:16:07,070
<i>Is he going to add a triple in the second half?</i>

263
00:16:09,130 --> 00:16:13,320
<i>Or is he going back to having three quads?</i>

264
00:16:14,120 --> 00:16:16,240
<i>Do you remember how I told you to focus</i>

265
00:16:16,240 --> 00:16:19,910
<i>more on refining the program 
than being distracted by jumps?</i>

266
00:16:24,530 --> 00:16:26,350
<i>You look too stiff!</i>

267
00:16:26,350 --> 00:16:30,170
<i>This is the part that expresses when 
I showed up as your coach, right?</i>

268
00:16:30,530 --> 00:16:33,300
<i>You look like you didn't like it at all!</i>

269
00:16:40,430 --> 00:16:41,520
<i>A triple Salchow?</i>

270
00:16:42,920 --> 00:16:45,450
<i>No, a quadruple! He stepped out of the landing.</i>

271
00:16:53,240 --> 00:16:56,490
<i>So he did revert the program 
to having three quads.</i>

272
00:16:58,110 --> 00:16:59,790
<i>Shake it off...</i>

273
00:16:59,790 --> 00:17:00,630
<i>Good!</i>

274
00:17:08,010 --> 00:17:09,490
<i>A triple loop!</i>

275
00:17:09,490 --> 00:17:11,380
<i>That was perfect.</i>

276
00:17:12,920 --> 00:17:15,510
<i>Now, Yuri's realized something like love.</i>

277
00:17:16,600 --> 00:17:19,750
<i>The second half's coming up, 
and he already looks tired.</i>

278
00:17:21,610 --> 00:17:23,270
<i>An outside spread eagle,</i>

279
00:17:25,280 --> 00:17:26,620
<i>then an Ina Bauer...</i>

280
00:17:27,790 --> 00:17:31,070
<i>Skate like you're the most beautiful 
person on the ice right now.</i>

281
00:17:33,610 --> 00:17:34,830
<i>A triple axel!</i>

282
00:17:35,890 --> 00:17:36,780
<i>Good, he hung in there.</i>

283
00:17:42,410 --> 00:17:44,090
<i>Next up, a triple flip!</i>

284
00:17:48,580 --> 00:17:51,100
<i>Even though he's not nailing his jumps,</i>

285
00:17:51,100 --> 00:17:53,250
<i>the audience is getting fired up...</i>

286
00:17:53,250 --> 00:17:56,260
<i>It's because he's skating in time with the music.</i>

287
00:18:00,930 --> 00:18:01,930
So close!

288
00:18:03,420 --> 00:18:05,730
<i>Yuri's being too impatient today.</i>

289
00:18:06,140 --> 00:18:08,660
<i>But that's why</i>

290
00:18:09,840 --> 00:18:11,690
<i>you can't look away!</i>

291
00:18:46,020 --> 00:18:50,030
<i>I told you to make the last jump 
a triple for the points...</i>

292
00:18:52,170 --> 00:18:57,670
<i>I wonder who he takes after, to be 
so rebellious toward his coach...</i>

293
00:19:05,070 --> 00:19:05,790
<i>Oh...</i>

294
00:19:07,250 --> 00:19:08,130
<i>It's me!</i>

295
00:19:13,850 --> 00:19:16,260
<i>If I were Yakov, it'd be an instant lecture.</i>

296
00:19:16,260 --> 00:19:17,760
<i>And I've done that, too, but...</i>

297
00:19:17,760 --> 00:19:18,550
Yuri-kun!

298
00:19:18,910 --> 00:19:21,800
He showed his pride as Japan's top skater!

299
00:19:20,320 --> 00:19:21,800
Yuri!!!

300
00:19:20,770 --> 00:19:22,450
Yuri!

301
00:19:44,200 --> 00:19:47,170
Victor!

302
00:19:47,170 --> 00:19:48,950
Oops, watch the nosebleed.

303
00:19:48,950 --> 00:19:54,220
The scores, please, for Katsuki Yuri-san. 
His free skate program score: 165.20.

304
00:19:54,220 --> 00:19:58,230
His total score: 259.56.

305
00:19:56,960 --> 00:20:00,610
It's amazing you scored that 
high after a jump like that!

306
00:19:58,230 --> 00:20:00,610
He is currently in first place.

307
00:20:00,610 --> 00:20:04,030
Thanks for proving to me that you're 
able to get a lot of PCS points.

308
00:20:04,030 --> 00:20:06,970
You can score even higher, 
so don't feel down, okay, Yuri?

309
00:20:06,970 --> 00:20:08,420
Yuri-kun!

310
00:20:08,830 --> 00:20:09,970
I totally lost to you.

311
00:20:10,400 --> 00:20:13,980
I want to face you in the 
Grand Prix series someday!

312
00:20:14,360 --> 00:20:16,480
Until then, please don't quit!

313
00:20:16,480 --> 00:20:17,900
And another thing!

314
00:20:18,220 --> 00:20:19,250
Please give me your autograph!

315
00:20:19,250 --> 00:20:19,740
Me, too!

316
00:20:19,740 --> 00:20:20,860
Can I take a photo with you?

317
00:20:21,310 --> 00:20:23,860
Yuri! I was so impressed!

318
00:20:24,330 --> 00:20:27,470
It was so obvious that you took the 
younger skaters seriously as rivals.

319
00:20:27,470 --> 00:20:30,250
What if you'd gotten hurt, slamming 
into the wall like that at the end?!

320
00:20:30,250 --> 00:20:32,190
S-Sorry.

321
00:20:32,810 --> 00:20:36,640
At first, I was just desperate 
because I didn't want to lose,

322
00:20:36,640 --> 00:20:40,260
but somehow, I started having 
a lot of fun in the middle.

323
00:20:40,610 --> 00:20:42,510
I don't remember a lot about it.

324
00:20:42,510 --> 00:20:43,590
Huh?

325
00:20:45,450 --> 00:20:46,140
Yeah...

326
00:20:48,690 --> 00:20:55,980
Anyway, that was the most fun I've ever 
had while skating in competition.

327
00:21:08,830 --> 00:21:10,680
What're you doing, Yuri?

328
00:21:10,680 --> 00:21:13,490
Oh, you saw the photo of Victor and 
the Japanese Yuri, didn't you?

329
00:21:13,490 --> 00:21:14,580
Jealous?

330
00:21:13,820 --> 00:21:15,080
Shut up, hag!

331
00:21:16,520 --> 00:21:18,720
Next, we have the skater Katsuki Yuri,

332
00:21:18,720 --> 00:21:22,420
who's thought to be the next leader 
of men's singles in Japan.

333
00:21:22,420 --> 00:21:24,090
Please, show us.

334
00:21:24,850 --> 00:21:28,100
Um... Please show your theme for this year.

335
00:21:28,100 --> 00:21:29,600
Skater Katsuki?

336
00:21:29,850 --> 00:21:31,850
Love 
Katsuki Yuri

337
00:21:32,780 --> 00:21:36,850
My theme in this year's 
Grand Prix series is "love."

338
00:21:38,060 --> 00:21:42,420
I've been helped by many people in my 
competitive skating career thus far,

339
00:21:42,420 --> 00:21:45,320
but I've never thought about "love" until now.

340
00:21:46,180 --> 00:21:49,010
Though I was blessed with support, 
I couldn't take full advantage of it.

341
00:21:49,010 --> 00:21:51,870
I always felt like I was fighting alone.

342
00:21:52,850 --> 00:21:55,280
But since Victor showed up to be my coach,

343
00:21:55,280 --> 00:21:57,290
I've seen something totally different.

344
00:21:58,690 --> 00:22:02,460
My "love" is not something 
clear-cut like romantic love,

345
00:22:02,460 --> 00:22:04,600
but the more abstract feeling 
of my relationships

346
00:22:04,600 --> 00:22:06,880
with Victor, family, and hometown...

347
00:22:07,430 --> 00:22:11,380
I was finally able to realize that something 
like love exists all around me.

348
00:22:12,760 --> 00:22:16,890
Victor is the first person I've 
ever wanted to hold on to.

349
00:22:17,860 --> 00:22:20,040
I don't really have a name for that emotion,

350
00:22:20,040 --> 00:22:22,650
but I have decided to call it "love."

351
00:22:22,650 --> 00:22:25,690
Now that I know what love 
is and am stronger for it,

352
00:22:25,690 --> 00:22:29,340
I'll prove it to myself with a 
Grand Prix Final gold medal!

353
00:22:33,050 --> 00:22:34,120
So we...

354
00:22:34,120 --> 00:22:35,720
...were abstract.

355
00:22:35,720 --> 00:22:37,700
After all this time we've supported him...

356
00:22:37,700 --> 00:22:40,670
When you come back, we'll burn that 
unfashionable necktie, Yuri.

357
00:22:41,400 --> 00:22:45,170
Let's buy a new one before the Cup of China.

358
00:22:48,660 --> 00:22:49,570
<i>Victor...</i>

359
00:22:50,090 --> 00:22:54,110
<i>Unfortunately for you, it won't be 
Yuri who wins the Cup of China.</i>

360
00:22:54,110 --> 00:22:56,060
<i>It will be Phichit Chulanont.</i>

361
00:22:56,390 --> 00:22:58,420
Wasn't that jump great?

362
00:22:58,420 --> 00:23:00,130
Did you get a good video of it?

363
00:23:00,130 --> 00:23:00,970
Oh, sorry...

364
00:23:00,970 --> 00:23:01,810
What?!

365
00:23:02,260 --> 00:23:06,820
We have to post it online as soon as possible!

366
00:23:06,820 --> 00:23:09,860
To Be Continued!!!

367
00:23:10,210 --> 00:23:10,860
Dajia hao!

368
00:23:10,860 --> 00:23:12,060
I want to eat Shanghai crab!

369
00:23:12,060 --> 00:23:14,360
Victor, our event is in Beijing.

370
00:23:14,360 --> 00:23:17,620
Crab, crab, shrimp, shrimp, xiao long bao!

371
00:23:17,620 --> 00:23:21,960
Next time, Sixth Skate: China's On! 
The Grand Prix Series Opening Event!!

372
00:23:19,830 --> 00:23:24,840
Sixth Skate 
China's On! The Grand Prix Series Opening Event!! 
The Cup of China Short Program

